##############################################
#
#         README for Line Tracer
#
#  Wellcome to the line tracer demo program.
#
##############################################

Line Tracer is a short compact set of classes
designed to show the operation of a line tracing
algorithm developed by


Luis Ibanez, 
Division of Neurosurgery
Medical Image Display and Analysis Group 
University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill
http://www.cs.unc.edu/~ibanez

Chafiaa Hamitouch, Christian Roux
Departement Image et Traitement de l'Information
ENST-Bretagne, France
http://www-iti.enst-bretagne.fr



This algorithm is suitable for tracing discrete
straight lines in regular grids of any dimension.


The implementation uses the MTL library
(Matrix Template Library) from:

Andrew Lumsdaine, Jeremy G.Siek, Lie-Quan Lee
University of Notre Dame
http://www.lsc.nd.edu/research/mtl

You need to download the MTL to be able to 
compile this code. (and eventually update
your C++ compiler)



